summary_markdown: This table presents a comparative analysis of credit card ownership demographics, broken down by gender and age groups across various credit card brands. The data is structured to show the percentage distribution of cardholders for each brand, with a specific focus on the male-to-female ratio and the age distribution across ten categories: 15-19, 20-24, 25-34, 35-44, 45-54, 55-64, and 65+. A consolidated "Average brand" row provides an aggregated view of these demographic percentages. The overall structure is comparative, allowing for direct observation of how different credit card brands align with specific gender and age segments of the consumer base.
